@pianoguy222  I would disagree. I would say that it's lesser.

 Big titles often aim to please everyone or as big an audience as they can garner, "spreading" the pleasure over a large coverage, reducing it's value. Niche titles target a specific group and stick to making sure that group gets the best experience they can bring to them, concentrating the pleasure into a small mark.

A title with "something for everyone"<  A title that means "everything to someone"
